main event: A UFO was tracked on radar traveling at high speeds over La Cala on 15 March 1961.
interesting points: The object was recorded moving in a straight line at approximately 1700 knots, which is significantly faster than a fighter aircraft., The object was detected at an altitude of approximately 60,000 feet., The radar blip indicated the object disappeared below the horizon after 8 minutes of observation., Visual observation was not possible during the sighting., The object was bearing 045 degrees and traveled in a south southwest direction.
witness description: Military personnel involved in ground-visual and air-visual radar observation.
